%spark
import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._


case class LikedBook(userId: Long, bookId: Long)
case class RecommendedBooks(userId: Long, books: Seq[Long])

implicit val likedBookEncoder = Encoders.product[LikedBook]
implicit val recommendedBooksEncoder = Encoders.product[RecommendedBooks]

val happyBookStream = spark
      .readStream
      .format("redis")                          
      .option("stream.keys", "books-liked")     
      .schema(likedBookEncoder.schema)
      .load()

%spark
val uId = 100L
val bId = 3L
val predictionCluster = books_publisher_ranked.where(col("id") === bId)
val avgRatingAndCount = predictionCluster.select("averageRating", "ratingsCount").map { case Row(a: Double, c: Long) => (a, c) }.collect().head
val cluster = predictionCluster.select("prediction").map { case Row(i: Int) => i }.collect().head


                
println(s"bookId=$bId cluster=$cluster")
val recommendedBooks = books_publisher_ranked
    .where(col("prediction").equalTo(cluster).and(col("id").notEqual(bId)))
    .select("id","title","averageRating")
    .limit(10)

val theBook = books_publisher_ranked.where(col("id") === bId)
val thePrediction = theBook.select("prediction").withColumnRenamed("prediction", "mapPrediction")
val genresForRank = thePrediction
    .join(genres_books_ranked)
    .where(col("mapPrediction").equalTo(col("prediction")).and(col("id").equalTo(bId)))
    .drop("mapPrediction")
    .groupBy("genreName")
    .agg(
        avg(col("averageRating")) as "avgRating",
        sum(col("userTaggedCount")) as "userTags",
        count("*") as "books"
    )
    .where(col("userTags") > 1000)
    .sort(desc("books"))
    .limit(5)

val selections = genresForRank.select("genreName").collect.map { case Row(s: String) => s }.toSeq

val topPerGenre = genres_books_ranked
    .groupBy("genreName","id")
    .agg(
        avg(col("averageRating")) as "avgRating",
        sum(col("userTaggedCount")) as "userTags",
        count("*") as "hits"
    )
    .sort(desc("hits"))

topPerGenre.createOrReplaceTempView("genre_toppers")

genresForRank.show(5, false)


/*
 For the book passed in
 Find the top5 genres associated with that book
 That match our same cluster (KMeans on publishers)
*/
val bestInGenre = genres_books_ranked
    .where(col("prediction").equalTo(cluster).and(col("id").notEqual(bId)).and(col("averageRating") >= avgRatingAndCount._1))
    .groupBy("genreName")
    .agg(
        avg(col("averageRating")) as "avgRating",
        sum(col("userTaggedCount")) as "userTags",
        count("*") as "books"
    )
    .where(col("userTags") > 1000)
    .sort(desc("userTags"))
    .limit(5)

val genres = bestInGenre.select("genreName").map { case Row(name: String) => name }.collect.toSeq

genres_books_ranked.where(col("genreName").isInCollection(genres).and(col("id").notEqual(bId))).createOrReplaceTempView("recommendations")

import spark.implicits._
import org.apache.spark.sql._

happyBookStream
    .writeStream
    .queryName("recommendations")
    .foreachBatch {
        (dataset: DataFrame, batchId: Long) => {
            val books_publisher_ranked = spark.read.parquet("/odsc/books_publisher_predictions.parquet")
            books_publisher_ranked.createOrReplaceTempView("books_publisher_ranked")
            books_publisher_ranked.printSchema
            val genres_books_ranked = spark.read.parquet("/odsc/genres_books_publishers_ranked.parquet")
            genres_books_ranked.printSchema
            genres_books_ranked.createOrReplaceTempView("genres_books_ranked")
            
            val recommendations = dataset.as[LikedBook].map { liked =>
                val bId = liked.bookId
                /*val theBook = books_publisher_ranked.where(col("id") === bId)
                val thePrediction = theBook.select("prediction").withColumnRenamed("prediction", "mapPrediction")
                val genresForRank = thePrediction
                    .join(genres_books_ranked)
                    .where(col("mapPrediction").equalTo(col("prediction")).and(col("id").equalTo(bId)))
                    .drop("mapPrediction")
                    .groupBy("genreName")
                    .agg(
                        avg(col("averageRating")) as "avgRating",
                        sum(col("userTaggedCount")) as "userTags",
                        count("*") as "books"
                    )
                    .where(col("userTags") > 10)
                    .sort(desc("books"))
                    .limit(5)
                val selections = genresForRank.select("genreName").collect.map { case Row(s: String) => s }.toSeq*/
                RecommendedBooks(liked.userId, Seq(3, 8, 20))
            }
            
            recommendations.write.mode("append").parquet(s"/odsc/recommendations/user_recommended_$batchId")
            
        }
    }
    .start()
